<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN226">
      <lg type="edition" style="pūṭṭuvil">
<l>ceṟṟaṉ ṟāyiṉuñ ceyirttaṉ ṟāyiṉu</l>
<l>muṟṟaṉ ṟāyiṉu muyviṉṟu mātō</l>
<l>pāṭunar pōlak kaitoḻu tētti</l>
<l>yiṟantaṉ ṟākal vēṇṭum polantār</l>
<l>maṇṭamar kaṭakkun tāṉait</l>
<l>tiṇṭēr vaḷavaṟ koṇṭa kūṟṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Even though it destroyed, even though it raged, (1)</l>
<l>  even though it had [him], is it really without escape? (2)</l>
<l>  – Death, that took Vaḷavaṉ with firm chariot (6)</l>
<l>  an army that was victorious in close battle, (5)</l>
<l>  [and] with a golden garland who wanted it to pass by, (4)</l>
<l>  praising with hands folded like the singers [do]. (3)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
